HEADWORD: Caponiere
<hw>Cap`o*niere"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>caponni⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, fr. Sp. <ets>caponera</ets>, orig., a cage
for fattening capons, hence, a place of refuge; cf. It.
<ets>capponiera</ets>. See <er>Capon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld>
<def>A work made across or in the ditch, to protect it from the enemy,
or to serve as a covered passageway.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caponize</ent>⟦br⟧
